features: 【Jumbo 2-tier Dish Rack 】Size:16.5(L)*11.3(W）*14.4(H) inch, (Note: Make sure the height between the countertop and cabinet is higher than 20 inch for better fitting dishes because the height of the rack is 14.4 inch)We also come with a 5.7 inch wide cutting board stand, a 10.2 inch wide storage box, and four movable hooks for better storage of other kitchen supplies.

【Free Up 60% of Kitchen Counter】Our dish drainer rack is big enough to accommodate all dishes, utensils, glasses and pots for a family of 4-6.(Approximately 10 plates, 16 bowls, 10 cups, 1 cutting board, 4 sets of knives and forks, 8 spoons or shovels)

【Auto-draining Drainboard】Automatic drainage at any time: Our dishrack is equipped with a 360 degree rotating telescopic bracket at the bottom, making it easy to drain in any direction and the most appropriate position for your needs., keeping the counter and dishwasher dry to avoid the breeding of bacteria, mosquitoes, and rust.

【Upgraded anti slip feet】Our large dish racks is equipped with 4 specially designed L-shaped non slip feet. The L-shaped metal feet give you enough height to easily wipe the countertop but without causing the rack to sway. This is something we have applied for a patent for, which other dishwashing racks do not have.

【Easy Installation, No Tools Needed】Forget the fuss of screws and tools; assembling our draining rack is a breeze. It's a quick and easy process, and all accessories are removable, allowing you to configure them in any direction that suits your needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great drying rack for dishes
reviews.reviewText: I wanted to get a double layer drying rack for a long timewhen I saw this, i knew i needed to try and i am very pleased with this productFirst it looks nice and not cheap - that is super important to me for anything that actually sits out on my countersecond, i love that there are so many options for drying different sized and shaped itemslast, i LOVE the drain - it really helps to make sure no excess water builds up

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great dish rack
reviews.reviewText: Assembly for this dish rack is super easy. Once assembled, the dish rack is very sturdy. I was concerned that the upper tier would be wobbly and I’d be afraid to put glasses up there but that’s not the case. This dish rack is really efficient in terms of space. I also like the feature of the rotating Drain spout. It’s nice that I can adjust where this sits on my countertop.

I liked the look of this product, but one look at that second tier in the product images, and I had my doubts about how stable it all would be. But after setting it up, my concerns were quickly alleviated; it's actually quite solid, especially loaded up. It's also nice to have so many options, as your can customise it to your current needs (rotating drain spout, removeable 2nd tier, setting the utensil basket outwards for more room, or inwards to make things more compact, ect). Great Product

reviews.reviewTitle: Sadly I Needed Help with Assembly
reviews.reviewText: This 2 tier dish rack was packaged well. The instructions were included and the bottom and base didn't really need any attention with exception of the drain spout.NOW I absolutely hate to admit this, but no matter how much I looked at the instructions, I could not for the life of me get the 2 sides to hook on. I will say I would have liked a bigger picture. Finally, I was so frustrated, I asked my husband to do it. I tried for 15 minutes and he did it in less than 2 minutes 🙄.The dish rack itself is solid and in no way flimsy for me. You'll see see have dishes in it that my husband did. I did mine a little different than he did. You have the option to hang the racks where you want and works best. The way we have our extra racks, you'll notice they hang past the dish drain, so you may have drips on your counter depending on the way you set it up.The overall size is a bit smaller in person than I had invisioned, but it definitely does the job!I do see it working best for a smaller family, or a family that has dishes that aren't dishwasher safe and need to hand wash. It has a nice look to it and price was, I thought it was fair. I have replaced my plastic one with this one, and it just has a nice sleeker look' as well no further concern for broken plastic slots thay don't keep my dishes upright4 stars... as it's a wee bit smaller than i anticipated, even though the dimensions were displayed. Also the fact the instructions could have been clearer for me!
